article.headline: Cornell 76, Stony Brook 72
article.story: ITHACA, N.Y. (AP) -- Andrew Naeve scored 20 points and Ryan Wittman had 18 to lead Cornell in a 76-72 win over Stony Brook in non-conference play Monday. Cornell (2-0) jumped out to a 44-35 halftime lead with 67 percent shooting from the floor. In the second half that fell to 51 percent from the floor, while Stony Brook finished with a 42.4 percent shooting average. Stony Brook (1-1) outrebounded Cornell 35-29. Mitchell Beauford had 24 points to lead Stony Brook and Ricky Lucas added 20. Emanuel Neto had a game-high 12 rebounds.
